RELEASING.md:13:## The version-string rule (anti-recurrence guard for C026)
RELEASING.md:15:Whenever the **draft** version changes (the `drafts/paper.md` header), **immediately** sync the version *strings* in `CITATION.cff` (`version`), `.zenodo.json` (`version` + title suffix), and `README.md` — even between deposits, with Zenodo paused. The metadata version string must never lag the draft. (DOIs are separate: headers cite the concept DOI; version DOIs are only swept on an actual deposit.) This drift recurred at v1.8→v1.12 (2026-07-10) exactly because the draft moved without a deposit.
