RELEASING.md:31:5. Zenodo new version on the deposition id in `_backups/zenodo-depid.txt` (a non-secret id). **Supply the API token through an environment variable at deposit time — `ZENODO_TOKEN`, exported into the shell session only (read it from your OS credential store / password manager) — never a token file left in the repo tree.** New-version draft → replace files (corpus + manuscript renders + code) → bump `version`/`publication_date` → publish → update the depid file.
RELEASING.md:37:- **Never persist it to a file in the working tree** (an earlier version of this flow named `_backups/zenodo-token.txt`; that pattern is retired). Pass it via `ZENODO_TOKEN` in the shell session, or a protected CI secret if the deposit is ever automated.
RELEASING.md:39:- Scope the token to the minimum needed (`deposit:write`, `deposit:actions`).
