 555: ## Implications for the architecture
 556: 
 557: 1. The funding-target closure rule earns its place as an
 558:    anti-concentration device (A027), but claims that it protects allocation
 559:    *quality* should not be made — the corpus does not make them, and the
 560:    simulation says it should not start.
 561: 2. The system-defined default rule (H033) and automatic allocation
 562:    profiles are not conveniences for disengaged citizens; they are the
 563:    principal carrier of allocation quality under realistic attention. The
 564:    architecture's honest position in D025 — designed, visible intermediation
 565:    — is quantitatively vindicated.
 566: 3. Because defaults are powerful, whoever sets Planning Scope weights holds
 567:    the quality of the whole allocation in their hands. The simulation puts a
 568:    number on the A020 agenda-setting limitation: it is worth more than any
 569:    feasible increase in citizen attention.
 570: 4. E4 sharpens point 3 into a constructive direction: the quality of the
 571:    weight vector is the binding constraint *whatever institution constructs
 572:    it*, fixed-bandwidth central construction does not scale, and aggregated
 573:    dispersed signals do — provided an aggregation institution exists (R3)
 574:    and signals are honest and unbiased (declared assumption). Open scope
 575:    construction moves from assumed impossibility to measured viability
 576:    with named preconditions; its elicitation mechanics remain gated by
 577:    A023.
 578: 5. E5 re-centers the whole evidence stack on the thesis: what the
 579:    architecture ultimately buys is delivered social value per unit of
 580:    budget. Selection and delivery compound multiplicatively, the full
 581:    system delivers 2.19× the zero-control opaque baseline (a lower
