 103: > **1.83 ≈ macro (1.05) × alloc (1.22) × delivery (1.43)**
 104: 
 105: read directly off the nested compounds — delivery = f_ver/f_weak = 0.86/0.60 = 1.43;
 106: alloc = (2-layer 1.74)/1.43 = 1.22; macro = (3-layer 1.83)/(2-layer 1.74) = 1.05. The
 107: measured compound equals the product of the marginal stage-gains — the empirical content
 108: of the O-ring form: **the stages multiply because they are serial and complementary.**
 109: Primary metric (oracle-normalized): **Δ₃ = +0.23 [MC 95% 0.21, 0.25]** — the distributed
 110: arm delivers 23 points more of the oracle's attainable value than the central
 111: (D̃ = 0.50 vs C̃ = 0.27). And β\*_pipe(η = 1) ≈ 0.2 > 0: at η = 1 the pipeline runs 1.44×
 112: (β = 0) → 0.84× (β = 0.3), crossing parity near β ≈ 0.2 — even a *fully accountable*
 113: central is beaten by a ~20-point delivery wedge δ.
